# CC-001 — Freeform Input Integration

## Goal

Integrate freeform questions into the existing identity engine while preserving canonical structure:

- freeform inputs → signals → tensions → reflection
- no breaking of existing deterministic signal system
- no overbuilding

---

## Read First (Required)

- docs/canon/question-bank-v1.md
- docs/canon/freeform-signal-extraction.md
- docs/canon/freeform-extraction-prompt.md
- docs/canon/signal-and-tension-model.md
- docs/canon/inner-constitution.md

---

## Scope

Add support for:

- Q-I1 (belief under disagreement)
- Q-I2 (epistemic flexibility)
- Q-I3 (belief under cost)

---

## Requirements

### 1. Question Flow

- Add freeform questions to the existing flow
- Render a textarea input instead of buttons
- Preserve:
  - question_id
  - card_id
  - question_text
  - response (string)

---

### 2. Freeform Storage

Ensure answers are stored in the same structure as other inputs:

```ts
{
  question_id: string,
  card_id: string,
  question_text: string,
  response: string,
  type: "freeform"
}